    uid=3_71 heading "Designed for how agents work" level="2"
    uid=3_72 StaticText "not for humans"
    uid=3_73 StaticText "Standard tools — Debugbar, Clockwork, Telescope — require a browser UI. LLM agents invoke commands, read JSON, and loop. laraperf is built around that model."
    uid=3_74 StaticText "Every command exits immediately"
    uid=3_75 StaticText "All output is structured JSON to stdout"
    uid=3_76 StaticText "Status/errors go to stderr — safe to pipe"
    uid=3_77 StaticText "Hashes let agents reference queries across commands"
    uid=3_78 StaticText "Stack traces filtered to"
    uid=3_79 StaticText "app/"
    uid=3_80 StaticText "— no vendor noise"
    uid=3_81 heading "Capture" level="3"
    uid=3_82 StaticText "perf:watch starts a session and returns immediately. DB::listen attaches to every PHP-FPM request automatically — the agent doesn't need to be watching."
    uid=3_83 heading "Analyse" level="3"
    uid=3_84 StaticText "perf:query reads the session and outputs a JSON summary: total queries, slow queries above a threshold, and N+1 candidates with count, table, and app-frame source location."
    uid=3_85 heading "Explain" level="3"
    uid=3_86 StaticText "perf:explain runs EXPLAIN (ANALYZE, BUFFERS, FORMAT JSON) on any SQL string or a 12-char hash from perf:query output. Non-SELECT statements are wrapped in BEGIN/ROLLBACK."
    uid=3_87 heading "N+1 Detection" level="3"
    uid=3_88 StaticText "Queries grouped by (batch_id, normalized_sql_hash). Structurally identical SQL with different literals is treated as the same query. Groups ≥ threshold reported as candidates."
    uid=3_89 heading "Stack trace filtering" level="3"
    uid=3_90 StaticText "Up to 5 frames per query, filtered to app/ and packages/ (excluding vendor). Filament/Eloquent queries report the Resource, Page, or RelationManager that triggered them."
    uid=3_91 heading "Multi-tenant support" level="3"
    uid=3_92 StaticText "--db flag patches the connection database at runtime and purges it. No changes to config/database.php, no dependency on any tenancy package."
    uid=3_93 link "Works with Agentation" url="https://agentation.com/"
      uid=3_94 StaticText "Works with Agentation"
    uid=3_95 StaticText "UI annotations for agents. Click any element, add a note, and paste the output into Claude Code, Codex, or any AI tool. Structured context for your agent."
    uid=3_96 heading "Typical agent workflow" level="2"
    uid=3_97 StaticText "Five steps from zero to a fixed query."
    uid=3_98 StaticText "1"
    uid=3_99 StaticText "perf:watch --seconds=120"
    uid=3_100 StaticText " — "
    uid=3_101 StaticText "start capture, get session ID back immediately"
    uid=3_102 StaticText "2"
    uid=3_103 StaticText "exercise the app — hit routes, run tests, seed data"
    uid=3_104 StaticText "3"
    uid=3_105 StaticText "perf:query --n1=3"
    uid=3_106 StaticText " — "
    uid=3_107 StaticText "get candidates with source file + line"
    uid=3_108 StaticText "4"
    uid=3_109 StaticText "perf:explain --hash=…"
    uid=3_110 StaticText " — "
    uid=3_111 StaticText "get query plan for the worst offender"
    uid=3_112 StaticText "5"
    uid=3_113 StaticText "fix, repeat until clean"
